cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about face detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also introduces novel two-step classification and regression operations, which involve machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper proposes a Receptive Field Enhancement (RFE) block, which involves image processing techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, since the paper deals with improving the accuracy and reducing false positives in face detection, it may also fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
